## 1. Zero Tolerance for Inline Styles & SCSS Hacks
- **Tailwind First:** ALWAYS use Tailwind CSS utility classes (e.g., `className="flex flex-col text-center"`).
- **NO SCSS Modules:** Do NOT create `.module.scss` files. Use Tailwind for all styling.
- **Mobile-First Tailwind:** Write default classes for mobile, use responsive prefixes (`md:`, `lg:`) for desktop.
- **Tailwind Config:** Use `tailwind.config.ts` for design tokens (colors, spacing, fonts) instead of magic numbers or CSS variables.
- **No !important:** Use Tailwind's specificity or clsx/tailwind-merge. Use `!important` ONLY when strictly necessary to override stubborn third-party styles.

## 2. Internationalization (i18n) First
- NEVER use hardcoded strings in the UI.
- ALWAYS use `next-intl` (e.g., `t('key')`) for all user-facing text.

## 3. Modern Next.js Architecture
- **Server Components Default:** Keep components as Server Components by default. Add `'use client'` ONLY at the top of files when interactivity or React hooks (useState, useEffect) are needed.
- **Images & Links:** Use Next.js `<Image>` (`next/image`) and `<Link>` (`next/link`) ONLY.
- **Fonts:** Use `next/font/google` or local fonts configured via Next.js.

## 4. UI Kit & Reusability (shadcn/ui First)
- **Check shadcn/ui First:** ALWAYS look in `@/components/ui/` (shadcn components) before reinventing wheels perfectly.
- If a standard component is missing, install it via CLI (e.g., `npx shadcn@latest add dialog`) rather than coding from scratch.
- **Mandatory Usage:** Use `<Button>` from `@/components/ui/button` (not raw `<button>` or `<a>`). Use shadcn `<Input>` and `<Form>` components for forms.

## 5. Strict TypeScript & Props
- **No `any`:** Strict zero tolerance for `any` types.
- **Interfaces:** Define `interface Props` or `type Props` for every component clearly.

## 6. Accessibility (a11y) & Semantics
- **Tags:** Use semantic HTML (`<nav>`, `<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`).
- **Labels:** Interactive elements without visible text (like icon buttons) MUST have `aria-label`.

## 7. Responsive Responsibility
- **Laptop Safe:** Navigation and essential content MUST be fully visible and functional on Laptops (1200px+).
- **Mobile Safe:** Ensure no horizontal overflow (`overflow-x-hidden`) on mobile screens.

## 8. Development Hygiene
- **Imports:** Use absolute paths (`@/components/...`, `@/lib/...`).
- **Cleanup:** Remove unused imports, variables, and `console.log` statements immediately.
- **Verify:** ALWAYS run `npm run build` before confirming major feature completions.

## 9. Clean Code Architecture (Separation of Concerns)
- **`src/app/`**: ONLY for Next.js routing, layouts, and page entry files (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`). Keep these files minimal. They should primarily fetch data and pass it to Section Components.
- **`src/components/ui/`**: ONLY for dumb, highly reusable, stateless components (e.g., shadcn buttons, inputs, modals). They should not fetch data or contain business logic.
- **`src/components/sections/`**: For large, page-specific functional blocks (e.g., `HeroSection`, `SpeakersShowcase`). These combine UI components and handle their own layout and animations (GSAP).
- **`src/lib/`**: For utility functions, helper methods, API fetchers, and configurations (e.g., `utils.ts`, `cn()`).
- **`src/hooks/`**: For custom React hooks (e.g., `useWindowSize`, `useGSAPTimeline`).
- **`src/data/`**: For mock data, constants, and structured JSON (e.g., `speakersData.ts`, `navigation.ts`). DO NOT put data directly inside components.
- **`src/types/`**: For global TypeScript interfaces and types shared across multiple files.
